{
  "answer": "**The matlaʿ (opening couplet) of the ghazal in chapter 200 of *Diwan-e-Ghalib*** is the first sher (couplet), which sets the radif \"samjha\" (understood/mistook) repeated throughout.[^1]\n\nIn transliteration:  \n**Woh meri cheen-e-jabeen se gham-e-pinhan samjha**  \n**Raaz-e-maktoob ba-be-rabti-e-unwan samjha**  \n\n(She mistook the furrow on my forehead for a hidden grief;  \nShe took the secret of the letter as unrelated to its heading.)\n\nThis ghazal explores themes of misunderstanding in love, where the beloved misinterprets the poet's signs of distress and passion.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [ch. 200](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/200-woh-meri-cheen-e-jabeen-se-gham-e-pinhan-samjha/transliteration/#p-966218).\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [ch. 200](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/200-woh-meri-cheen-e-jabeen-se-gham-e-pinhan-samjha/transliteration/).",
